peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is the most expensive piggy bank in the world?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: It has unveiled the world's most expensive piggy bank - an 18-carat gold design costing £100,000. Bristol-based silversmiths Phillip Kydd and his son James have created the model, which is part of a range of piggy banks called Minty.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: Should I keep a piggy bank?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: It's okay to have a piggy bank when you're younger or have money hidden underneath your, in your sock drawer, but as you start getting older, you want to start having that in a more secure place that you can utilize it how you see fit.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is the oldest piggy bank?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The earliest known pig-shaped money containers date to the 12th century on the island of Java. The Javanese term cèlèngan (ꦕꦺꦭꦺꦁꦔꦤ꧀; literally "likeness of a wild boar", but used to mean both "savings" and "piggy bank") is also in the modern Indonesian language.
